						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the Kanakāmbikā shrine in the Madhyasthanāthēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Duṉmukhi.</p>						

						<p>The details of date given are Duṉmukhi, Kāttigai, 25. Palaeographically this inscription may be assigned to the 18th century.</p>						

						<p>It mentions the desolation of the <hi rend="italic">paṟṟu</hi> on account of the death of Rāyar and the measures taken by the <hi rend="italic">mahājaṉas</hi> and <hi rend="italic">tāṉattār</hi> of the place for the god consecrated by the Mudalis of Āṟagaḷūr. This inscription is unfinished.</p>						

						</summary>
